Unknown gunmen on Tuesday killed one and abducted two family members of Salisu Usman-Maku, elder brother to Labaran Maku, a former Minister of Information. A family member told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Lafia that the gunmen stormed their house at Gudi village of Akwanga Local Government Area in the early hours of Tuesday. The source said the gunmen killed their sister and kidnapped their brother, who is an officer with the Nigeria Immigration Service and his wife. Comptroller of Immigration in the state, Zainab Lawal, confirmed the incidence of the kidnap of their staff, Salihu Usman-Maku and his wife. “Nigeria Immigration Officer (NIS) Supt. Salisu Usman and his wife were abducted at gunpoint on Tuesday,” She said.